          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 82,
              "body": "Using lower-case should/must will lead to questions of whether it should be upper-case SHOULD/MUST, but we were trying to avoid normative language in this section.  What if I change it to the following to make it sound less prescriptive, but rather a justification of why the use case is appropriate?\r\n\r\n> In each of these cases, the operator is able to control their signing environment such that signatures can be generated in hardware cryptographic modules and audited before the signature is published, in order to prevent OTS key reuse.",
              "createdAt": "2024-09-19T15:04:46Z",
              "updatedAt": "2024-09-19T15:04:46Z"
            }
          ]
        },
